    {
      "id": "bfc15a132739842927422978b623bca89a26cabe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-02-25 15:54:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nSo, lockless truncate is very broken - There are some details here:\nhttps://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10059\nAnd not easily fixable, as far as I could tell (This is just the bug I found, it doesn't cover the original issues that led to it being switched off in early 2.x).  I think it would be the same for DoM/MDC, though haven't considered in detail.\n\nAnd I'm not sure lockless i/o in general works either.  I think if it were to turn on, we'd have some of the same issues as with lockless truncate(?).  My memory is it's almost impossible to trigger lockless mode on the OSC/extent side.  Makes me nervous about the idea of enabling it for DoM.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
